{
  "stem": "8784.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I continued working at Oskar Schindler's factory.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, this work continued until March 12, 1943.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We would be marching out daily from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And on March 12, we-- I walked out of the ghetto, saying goodbye to my family as I normally would when I left for work.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But on March 12 when we got to Oskar Schindler's factory, Oskar Schindler announced to the group that we cannot go back to the ghetto, that the ghetto is being liquidated, that there is an Aktion in the ghetto itself, meaning that people are being killed there.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There is-- there are brutalities going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "People are taken away from there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we would be better off staying in his factory than going back to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There is a good chance that at that time that he had the option.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He had the option of delivering us to the ghetto and therefore delivering us to be exposed to the, all the brutalities that were going on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Or he had the chance to make a quick decision that he's going to keep us over.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he made the decision to keep us over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And while we were staying there for the next three or four nights at the factory, sleeping on the, on the floor or wherever we could find a place in the factory, as we know now-- at that time we didn't know that-- but in fact, the Germans had decided to liquidate the Cracow ghetto.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They entered with extreme, extremely well-armed squadrons of, of SS.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they began to kill and take out people to be shipped to other concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was, indeed, the last time that I saw my family.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
